main event: On October 11, 1951, multiple unidentified flying objects were observed over Minneapolis, Minnesota, exhibiting erratic behavior, high speeds, and agility.
interesting points: The objects were observed at 0530 and again two hours later, moving too fast to be tracked with a theodolite and leaving no vapor trails.
The objects appeared to be glowing brightly, with a pale yellow or amber color, and moved in a circular motion before rapidly changing directions.
Pilots observed a brightly glowing object with a halo around it, displaying rapid and erratic movements before disappearing to the east.
Observers confirmed the objects had a definite shape, no visible trails or jet propulsion, and traveled at extremely high speeds and altitude.

The intelligence background of the observers and the presence of multiple witnesses added credibility to the sightings, leading to the classification of these incidents as Unidentified Aerial Phenomena.
sighted object: Multiple unidentified flying objects exhibiting erratic behavior and glowing appearance
witnesses: Experienced pilots, ground observers, and airport operators
photographs: No photographs were included in the report
